responded: Perfect! I found it. On line 5051-5052, there's the case for `Opcode::kLoadRootRegister` which calls `VisitLoadRootRegister(node)`. This is in the Turboshaft adapter version of the VisitNode function.

Now I understand the issue. The problem is that the `VisitLoadRootRegister` function contains `UNREACHABLE()`, but it's actually being called. According to the comment in the function, it should "Do nothing" because following loads/stores will use `kMode_Root` to load/store from an offset of the root register.

The fix should be to remove the `UNREACHABLE()` and make the function actually do nothing, as the comment suggests. Let me create the patch:

args.patch:
diff --git a/src/compiler/backend/instruction-selector.cc b/src/compiler/backend/instruction-selector.cc
index 28468a70790..dc66842c0f1 100644
--- a/src/compiler/backend/instruction-selector.cc
+++ b/src/compiler/backend/instruction-selector.cc
@@ -1848,7 +1848,6 @@ template <typename Adapter>
 void InstructionSelectorT<Adapter>::VisitLoadRootRegister(node_t node) {
   // Do nothing. Following loads/stores from this operator will use kMode_Root
   // to load/store from an offset of the root register.
-  UNREACHABLE();
 }

 template <typename Adapter>

